Roarke comes and says that he is experiencing his&nbsp;
own fantasy of reuniting with his departed wife,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:08.720 --> 00:01:13.040
and that it will be realised as long as the&nbsp;
visitors' wishes are met. Roarke is persuaded&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:13.040 --> 00:01:18.240
by Gwen to modify her fantasy. Meanwhile,&nbsp;
Patrick is apprehended by American soldiers,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:18.240 --> 00:01:22.240
who present him to Lieutenant Sullivan,&nbsp;
their commander. Although Sullivan does&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:22.240 --> 00:01:26.720
not recognise him, Patrick knows that he is his&nbsp;
father, on his final assignment before dying.

00:01:27.280 --> 00:01:32.000
As night falls, the surgeon attacks Melanie and&nbsp;
Sloane once more before being murdered by Damon,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:32.000 --> 00:01:35.760
an island private investigator.&nbsp;
Damon leads them to a cave,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:35.760 --> 00:01:40.240
explaining that the fancies are caused by&nbsp;
spring water beneath a shining rock. Damon&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:40.240 --> 00:01:44.560
explains that he came to investigate until Roarke&nbsp;
granted him a wish to see his dead daughter,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:44.560 --> 00:01:47.600
but the fantasy turned into a&nbsp;
nightmare, trapping him on the island.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:48.160 --> 00:01:52.080
The three collects some spring water before&nbsp;
proceeding to the resort to seek assistance.

00:01:52.720 --> 00:01:57.200
However, as J. D. and Brax are kidnapped by a&nbsp;
drug gang linked to the mansion's owner, and&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:01:57.200 --> 00:02:01.520
Gwen is sent back to the night she inadvertently&nbsp;
set a fire that killed her neighbour Nick Taylor,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:01.520 --> 00:02:06.560
Fantasy Island begins to transform the other&nbsp;
dreams into nightmares. Except for Melanie,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:11.280
she discovers that all of the other visitors were&nbsp;
