00:02:11.280 --> 00:02:16.640
to save Nick, and she is saved by Julia, Roarke's&nbsp;
personal assistant. Sullivan's troops are also&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:16.640 --> 00:02:22.000
dispatched to save some captives, who turn out&nbsp;
to be J. D. and Brax. The cartel reanimates as&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:27.440
zombies after being killed, attacking the troops.&nbsp;
J. D. is killed in the subsequent pandemonium,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:27.440 --> 00:02:31.360
and Sullivan sacrifices himself so that&nbsp;
his son and Brax can return to the resort.

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.640
Melanie and Sloane are assaulted by the zombified&nbsp;
surgeon until Damon saves them by leaping over a&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:36.640 --> 00:02:41.760
cliff beside him. The remaining guests reunite&nbsp;
at the resort, but are confronted by Roarke,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:41.760 --> 00:02:44.880
who explains that they are all being&nbsp;
slaughtered as part of someone else's dream.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:45.520 --> 00:02:49.920
The visitors assume that this is Roarke's dream,&nbsp;
believing that he and Julia are Nick's parents,&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:49.920 --> 00:02:54.720
after realising that everyone was complicit in&nbsp;
Nick's killing. The guests flee to the pier in the&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:54.720 --> 00:02:59.840
hopes of being rescued by an aircraft dispatched&nbsp;
by Damon's colleagues, but the plane is shot down.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:02:59.840 --> 00:03:04.160
With a grenade carried by Patrick, the gang&nbsp;
rushes to the cave to blast the glowing rock.

00:03:04.880 --> 00:03:09.360
Melanie stabbings and wounds Patrick before&nbsp;
kidnapping Sloane. She confesses that this is&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:09.360 --> 00:03:13.840
her actual fantasy, having staged the tournament&nbsp;
in order to get revenge on the guests for Nick's&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:13.840 --> 00:03:18.400
murder, with whom she was meant to be on a date&nbsp;
the night he died; Julia is also revealed to be&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:18.400 --> 00:03:23.840
Roarke's wife. When Julia begins to deteriorate,&nbsp;
she persuades Roarke to assist his visitors in&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:23.840 --> 00:03:28.880
escaping the island before she vanishes. Sloane&nbsp;
drinks the spring water she collected earlier&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:28.880 --> 00:03:33.520
and fantasises about Melanie and Nick being&nbsp;
together. Melanie is dragged into the sea&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:33.520 --> 00:03:38.560
by Nick's zombified body as a result of this.&nbsp;
Melanie detonates the device against the guests&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:38.560 --> 00:03:42.960
before drowning, but Patrick makes the ultimate&nbsp;
sacrifice by falling on it to save the others.

00:03:43.680 --> 00:03:47.920
Gwen, Sloane, and Brax wake up at the&nbsp;
resort, where Roarke offers to let them go.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:48.560 --> 00:03:52.000
Brax asks for J. D. to come back to&nbsp;
life and return home as the three&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:52.000 --> 00:03:55.280
survivors board a plane to leave&nbsp;
the now-purified Fantasy Island.&nbsp;&nbsp;

00:03:55.840 --> 00:03:59.840
Roarke says that in order for Brax's fantasy&nbsp;
